news.title: Maharashtra to build 3.75 lakh houses under PMAY-Urban till December 2024
news.para: These 3.75 lakh units are a part of the 15.82 lakh units sanctioned for the state in 2015, of which 6.93 lakh or 44% have been completed. The earlier deadline to complete the construction of the 2015 target was 2022, which was revised to 2024 in the Centre's bid to offset the impact of Covid-19 pandemic.

news.title: Property dealer forges papers for Haryana RERA certification, registration revoked
news.para: Vineet Kejriwal had forged documents and signatures of an engineer to show the latter’s office — RND Projects — in Bristol hotel as his rented office.

news.title: Noida authority directs Supertech to remove twin towers' debris in 45 days
news.para: Work on removing the rubble had stopped for about a month after a UP Pollution Control Board (UPPCB) report revealed that the sound level from the use of concrete breakers at the site was on the higher side.

news.title: Gurugram: CBRI set to carry out second audit at Chintels Paradiso
news.para: In November last year, DC Nishant Yadav ordered the flattening of the highrise building on the basis of IIT-Delhi’s recommendation. The CBI is currently investigating the collapse of the flats.

news.title: Builders in Noida plead with SC to recall order on rate of interest
news.para: The controversy on rate of interest has been going round in circles for the last three years. First the Supreme Court in June 2020 reduced the rate of interest, which was in the vicinity of 15%-23%, depending on the terms of contract and capped it at 8%.

news.title: Gaming tech firm Aristocrat leases 128,000 sq ft of office space at Noida SEZ
news.para: The leasing comes at a time when companies are avoiding SEZs and are waiting for the Development (Enterprise and Services) Hubs Bill, 2022, to replace the Special Economic Zones Act. Samsung had leased 370,000 sq ft of office space at Candor TechSpace SEZ, which is part of the Brookfield REIT portfolio.

news.title: Icertis' co-founder buys apartment in Mumbai's Juhu for Rs 38 crore
news.para: The deal values the apartment with carpet area of 3,055 sq ft at over Rs 1.24 lakh per sq ft, a high for the locality known for the properties of Bollywood actors, directors, and producers. Given the per sq ft rate, the transaction will also enter the  tally of most expensive residential deals in the country.

news.title: GST cut on cement may be put on fitment panel's table, says Finance Minister
news.para: "I see your point. Let's say we have the fitment committee look into it and, if necessary, take it to the council," the minister said, responding to a suggestion from the infrastructure industry to lower the GST rate on cement on the grounds that it would lower project costs and spur growth.

news.title: Brookfield India REIT declares flat payout at Rs 5 per unit
news.para: Brookfield REIT, the only fully-institutionally managed REIT in the country, said it achieved gross leasing of 3.32 million square feet (sf) in the quarter, including 2,41,000 sf of new leasing and 91,000 sf of renewals.

news.title: IndiaBulls Home Loans, Kissht among websites blocked by government
news.para: The list includes www.indiabullshomeloans.com operated by housing finance company Indiabulls Housing Finance Ltd and Kissht.com which is operated by RBI registered NBFC firm ONEMi Technology Solutions Private Limited.

news.title: Haryana RERA forfeits bank guarantees of JMS Infra Realty
news.para: A​s per the conditions for granting RERA registration certificate (RC) in March 2022, the promoter had to submit the approved service plans and estimates and the approved zoning plan of the project within three months.

news.title: Sobha's net profit dips by 47.87% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Sobha's consolidated total income stood at Rs 898 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 38.15 per cent from Rs 650 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: The Phoenix Mills posts net profit of Rs 212.39 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: The Phoenix Mills' consolidated total income stood at Rs 718.57 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 60.75 per cent from Rs 447 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Sebi to auction properties of six firms on March 3 to recover investors' money
news.para: Apart from MPS Group and Tower Infotech, the regulator has put on block properties of Vibgyor Group, Prayag Group, Multipurpose BIOS India Group and Waris Finance International Group.

news.title: Bombay HC seeks to know if MahaRERA can identify, classify & rate builders
news.para: ​A division bench of Justices Gautam Patel and Neela Gokhale was on February 3 hearing a petition taken up suo motu (on its own) by the HC based on a plea filed by a person seeking payment of unpaid transit rent and against the stalled redevelopment of a cessed property known as 'Ratilal Mansion' in south Mumbai.
